==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Teneral
<hw>Ten"er*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>tener</ets>, <ets>-eris</ets>, tender, delicate.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Of, pertaining to, or designating, a condition
assumed by the imago of certain Neuroptera, after exclusion from the
pupa. In this state the insect is soft, and has not fully attained its
mature coloring.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Teneriffe</ent>⟦br⟧
